0other%20people's%20experiences.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20think%20a%20large%20part%20of%20my%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freading-specialist-shares-what-she-wishes-parents-knew-about-literacy-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Egrowing%20up%20to%20be%20a%20reader%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20because%20I%20saw%20my%20aunt%20and%20uncle%20reading%20all%20the%20time%2C%20and%20I%20can%20remember%20asking%20them%20similar%20questions.%20I%20didn't%20like%20reading%20for%20a%20long%20time%2C%20but%20when%20I%20asked%20my%20aunt%20to%20help%20me%20find%20books%20that%20I%20liked%2C%20and%20she%20did%2C%20that%20was%20it.%20I%20was%20hooked%2C%20and%20I%20loved%20getting%20to%20sit%20around%20and%20read%20with%20them%2C%20as%20if%20I%20had%20joined%20the%20club.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2259539a31-7833-4ec7-b4c0-b2f9d6774da0%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20always%20tell%20parents%20to%20read%20with%20their%20children%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20have%20found%20that%20many%20parents%20don't%20realize%20reading%20to%20their%20children%20is%20just%20as%20beneficial%20as%20a%20child%20reading%20on%20their%20own.%20When%20you%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbenefits-reading-to-kids-2017-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eread%20to%20your%20child%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20they%20are%20still%20experiencing%20the%20story%2C%20being%20exposed%20to%20new%20vocabulary%2C%20and%20listening%20to%20how%20you%20read.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20have%20always%20read%20to%20my%20son%20nightly.%20At%20times%20of%20frustration%20when%20he%20doesn't%20want%20to%20read%20on%20his%20own%2C%20I%20have%20found%20solace%20in%20the%20fact%20that%20he%20still%20looks%20forward%20to%20our%20nightly%20reads.%20It%20helps%20me%20acknowledge%20that%20maybe%20there's%20a%20reader%20in%20him%20that%20