r%20employers%20today.%20I%20think%20that's%20because%20the%20world%20expects%20more%20from%20people%20than%20ever%20before.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20my%20father's%20generation%20of%20the%201950s%20and%2060s%2C%20a%20sense%20of%20gratitude%20and%20subservience%20was%20culturally%20prevalent.%20People%20were%20pleased%20to%20have%20a%20job%20and%20were%20often%20there%20for%20life.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20generation%20of%20the%201980s%20was%20grateful%20for%20our%20jobs%20and%20believed%20that%20if%20you%20worked%20hard%2C%20you'd%20get%20on.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20daughters%20are%20both%20in%20their%20mid-20s.%20Their%20generation%20knows%20that%20they%20need%20to%20work%20hard%20to%20progress%2C%20but%20their%20employer%20also%20needs%20to%20work%20hard%20for%20them%20to%20stay.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20younger%20generation%20wants%20to%20work%20in%20a%20place%20that%20gives%20back%20to%20society%2C%20does%20the%20right%20thing%20in%20the%20right%20ways%2C%20and%20treats%20staff%20well.%20They%20will%20not%20tolerate%20chauvinism%2C%20sexism%2C%20unfairness%2C%20or%20bias%20%E2%80%94%20and%20quite%20rightly.%20They%20expect%20more%20than%20my%20generation%20and%20certainly%20more%20than%20my%20parents'%20generation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20generation%20under%2035%20is%20not%20prepared%20to%20tolerate%20a%20lack%20of%20opportunity%20as%20much%20as%20my%20generation.%20Individuals%20want%20to%20grow%2C%20to%20add%20value%2C%20and%20to%20be%20recognized.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20an%20accountancy%20firm%20where%20I%20worked%2C%20they%20would%20refer%20to%20their%20fresh%20intake%20of%20college%20graduates%20as%20%26quot%3Bthe%20L'Oreal%20generation%26quot%3B%20because%20%26quot%3Bthey're%20worth%20it.%26quot%3B%20My%20daughters'%20generation%20believes%20that%20they%20are%20worth%20it.%20That's%20a%20great%20thing%2C%20particularly%20for%20young%20women.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b09f8741-26c0-4d8f-99fe-30fdc78187a9%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3EWorkplaces%20have%20become%20more%20accepting%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEmployees'%20growing%20expectations%20push%20change%20because%20employers%2C%20caught%20in%20the%20so-called%20%26quot%3Bwar%20for%20talent%2C%26quot%3B%20need%20to%20meet%20them%20to%20retain%20their%20workforce.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWorkplaces%20have%20become%20more%20accepting.%20People%20of%20all%20backgrounds%2C%20creeds%2C%20nationalities%2C%20genders%2C%20and%20sexual%20orientations%20are%20embraced%20more%20than%20ever%20before.%20When%20I%20started%20working%2C%20an%20employer%20openly%20supporting%20Pride%20was%20unheard%20of.%20Fortunately%2C%20that's%20no%20longer%20the%20case.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20acceptance%20is%20reflected%20in%20companies'%20policies%2C%20while%20there's%20more%20open%20discussion%20around%20mental%20health%20and%20the%20importance%20of%20speaking%20up.%20There's%20a%20greater%20intolerance%20for%20poor%20practice%2C%20a%20desire%20to%20get%20it%20right%2C%20and%20more%20investment%20in%20training%2C%20support%2C%20coaching%2C%20and%20mentoring.%20It%20reflects%20a%20wider%20shift%20in%20society.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20used%20to%20work%20in%20finance%20in%20London%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20City%2C%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20late%2080s%20and%20early%2090s.%20It%20wasn't%20a%20million%20miles%20away%20from%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwolf-of-wall-street-review-2013-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Wolf%20of%20Wall%20Street.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20swore%20blind%20to%20myself%20that%20my%20daughters%20would%20not%20walk%20into%20a%20workplace%20with%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fmedia%2F2015%2Fjan%2F19%2Fhas-the-sun-axed-page-3-topless-pictures%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EPage%203%20calendars%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20the%20notice%20board%2C%20where%20men%20openly%20discuss%20their%20lewd%20behavior.%20There%20has%20been%20some%20progress.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20are%20still%20strands%20of%20that%20behavior%20that%20exist%20in%20certain%20sectors.%20There%20is%20still%20a%20male%20hierarchy%20in%20banking%2C%20insurance%2C%20financial%20services%2C%20and%20many%20other%20industries.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20is%20still%20an%20institutionalized%20bias%20against%20women%20or%20people%20of%20different%20ethnic%20backgrounds.%20You%20only%20have%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hrmagazine.co.uk%2Fcontent%2Fnews%2Fpushy-solicitor-wins-unfair-dismissal-tribunal%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Elook%20at%20employment%20tribunal%20hearings%20to%20see%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%94%20and%20that's%20the%20stuff%20that's%20public.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f82ec925-88ba-4bb3-ac46-fcbf663452ff%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3EEmployees%20are%20in%20danger%20of%20losing%20relationship-building%20skills%20at%20work%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20technology%20has%20developed%2C%20I%20think%20digital%20skills%20have%20been%20prioritized%20over%20more%20traditional%20social%20and%20relationship-building%20skills.%20We've%20denied%20younger%20generations%20the%20benefits%20of%20socialization%20in%20the%20workplace.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIncreased%20hybrid%20and%20remote%20working%20since%20the%20pandemic%20has%20mainly%20had%20a%20positive%20effect%2C%20but%20I%20do%20think%20the%20negative%20consequences%20are%20often%20underestimated%2C%20both%20from%20a%20mental%20health%20and%20productivity%20perspective.%20Management%20and%20measurement%20at%20work%20are%20still%20necessary%2C%20and%20hybrid%20working%20does%20not%20allow%20for%20that%20in%20the%20same%20way.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20benefits%20of%20being%20in%20a%20physical%20workplace%20environment%20are%20huge.%20Hybrid%20working%20can%20negate%20some%20of%20the%20advantages%20of%20coming%20together.%20This%20needs%20to%20be%20managed%20by%20having%20more%20of%20a%20return%20to%20the%20previous%20work%20environment%20and%20with%20more%20collaborative%20working%20arrangements.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f849a1df-ed88-4728-a70a-dc5c8eef89a0%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3EEmployees%20have%20a%20healthier%20work-life%20balance%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYounger%20generations%20expect%20not%20to%20work%20beyond%20their%20contracted%20hours%20and%20expect%20to%20be%20rewarded%20well.%20The%20ability%20to%20set%20boundaries%20is%20absolutely%20a%20good%20thing.%20I%20think%20it%20promotes%20more%20efficient%20and%20smarter%20ways%20of%20working.%20But%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20I%20think%20it%20needs%20to%20be%20managed.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20my%20dinosaur%20view%2C%20I%20think%20the%20dial%20has%20gone%20too%20far%20in%20favor%20of%20employees.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMost%20of%20us%20signed%20contracts%20to%20work%20in%20an%20office%2C%20Monday%20to%20Friday.%20Employees%20who%20are%20unhappy%20about%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnothing-smartphone-maker-staff-return-to-the-office-full-time-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereturning%20to%20the%20workplace%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20should%20be%20tackled%20quite%20strongly%2C%20I%20believe.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20you%20cross%20the%20white%20line%20at%20a%20golf%20club%2C%20you're%20asked%20to%20play%20by%20the%20rules%20of%20that%20golf%20club.%20The%20needs%20and%20interests%20of%20the%20business%20should%20be%20of%20equal%20c