el%20in%20Asia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKeay%20receives%20over%20%242%2C900%20monthly%20from%20his%20military%20retirement%20pension%20in%20addition%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboomer-military-veteran-raised-kids-germany-retired-texas-social-security-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emonthly%20pension%20for%20veterans%20with%20disabilities%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20also%20receives%20payouts%20from%20investments%20he%20made%20earlier%20in%20a%20Vanguard%20Mutual%20Fund%20and%20money%20from%20selling%20his%20home%20in%20Germany.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20disability%20pay%20combined%20with%20my%20retirement%20makes%20living%20at%20my%20age%20very%20comfortable%2C%26quot%3B%20Keay%20said.%20%26quot%3BWith%20that%20money%2C%20I%20definitely%20have%20not%20only%20security%20but%20also%20financial%20independence.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKeay%20is%20one%20of%20nearly%20a%20thousand%20Army%20retirees%20to%20settle%20in%20South%20Korea.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%20country%20was%20home%20to%20908%20US%20Army%20retirees%20in%20September%202022%2C%20the%20second-largest%20amount%20for%20any%20country%20outside%20the%20US%20after%20Germany%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmedia.defense.gov%2F2023%2FOct%2F06%2F2003315292%2F-1%2F-1%2F0%2FMRS%2520STATRPT%25202022%2520V999.PDF%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDepartment%20of%20Defense%3C%2Fa%3E%20report%20published%20in%20October%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKeay%20said%20living%20in%20South%20Korea%20provides%20him%20with%20better%20healthcare%20and%20quality%20of%20life.%20What's%20more%2C%20he%20doesn't%20think%20he%20would%20have%20the%20same%20disposable%20income%20if%20he%20lived%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220df13ce0-d29e-46c7-9def-4eb8712dd5ff%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20childhood%20interest%20in%20the%20military%20sparked%20a%20career%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EKeay%20was%20born%20in%20Malvern%2C%20a%20town%20in%20Worcestershire%2C%20England%2C%20and%20was%20raised%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Fplace%2FWest-Germany%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWest%20Germany%3C%2Fa%3E.%20His%20father%20was%20a%20member%20of%20the%20English%20Royal%20Air%20Force%20and%20served%20in%20WWII.%20From%20a%20young%20age%2C%20Keay%20was%20fascinated%20with%20the%20military%20and%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201989%2C%20while%20living%20in%20Germany%2C%20Keay%20met%20his%20ex-wife%2C%20who%20was%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ea%20US%20soldier.%20A%20year%20later%2C%20Keay%20moved%20to%20Alabama%20with%20her%2C%20and%20he%20enlisted%20in%20the%20US%20Army%20in%201992.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%2010%20years%2C%20Keay%20was%20stationed%20in%20various%20states%20in%20the%20US%20and%20he%20obtained%20his%20US%20citizenship%2C%20he%20said.%20Then%2C%20in%202002%2C%20he%20was%20assigned%20to%20outposts%20in%20Germany%20and%20the%20Netherlands.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Keay%20retired%20from%20the%20US%20Army%2C%20he%20said%20he%20had%20no%20intention%20of%20returning%20to%20the%20US.%20Meanwhile%2C%20he%20and%20his%20first%20wife%20divorced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202016%2C%20Keay%20visited%20Yongsan%2C%20South%20Korea%2C%20a%20district%20in%20Seoul%2C%20where%20he%20met%20his%20current%20wife%20Mi%20ok%20Jeon.%20While%20they%20initially%20lived%20in%20Germany%2C%20Mi%20ok%20had%20difficulty%20adjusting%20to%20life%20in%20Waurichen%2C%20a%20small%20village%20near%20Germany's%20border%20with%20Belgium%20and%20the%20Netherlands%2C%20he%20said.%20Additionally%2C%20her%20son%2C%20who%20lived%20in%20South%20Korea%2C%20had%20a%20child%20and%20she%20wanted%20to%20be%20closer%20to%20her%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221f1bf490-9c05-44a2-970a-14461a5ea37c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELife%20in%20South%20Korea%20is%20convenient%20and%20efficient%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20Keay%20sold%20the%20home%20he%20bought%20in%20Waurichen%20in%202005%2C%20and%20the%20couple%20moved%20to%20%3Ca%2