3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FVKHSU%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22The%20most%20worker-friendly%20states%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22522%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Oxfam%20report%20looks%20at%20three%20dimensions%20of%20what%20makes%20a%20state%20worker-friendly%3A%20Wages%2C%20worker%20protections%2C%20and%20the%20right%20to%20organize.%20Wages%20are%20weighted%20the%20most%20out%20of%20those%20three%20categories%3B%20key%20policies%20tracked%20in%20that%20dimension%20include%20the%20ratio%20of%20the%20state%20minimum%20wage%20to%20the%20wage%20needed%20to%20sustain%20a%20household%20of%20four%2C%20that%20same%20ratio%20for%20unemployment%20payments%2C%20and%20whether%20the%20state%20lets%20its%20localities%20have%20control%20over%20raising%20their%20minimum%20wages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorker%20protection%20makes%20up%2035%25%20of%20the%20score%3B%20key%20policies%20factored%20into%20the%20ranking%20include%20equal%20pay%20mandates%20targeting%20the%20gender%20pay%20gap%2C%20paid%20sick%20and%20family%20leave%2C%20child%20labor%20protections%2C%20limiting%20quotas%20for%20warehouse%20workers%2C%20and%20heat%20safety%20standards.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%2C%20finally%2C%20the%20right%20to%20organize%20makes%20up%2025%25%20of%20the%20total%20composite%20score.%20The%20key%20policies%20Oxfam%20tracks%20there%20include%20whether%20states%20have%20right-to-work%20laws%2C%20which%20allow%20workers%20to%20opt%20out%20of%20joining%20unions%20but%20still%20benefit%20from%20their%20contracts%2C%20whether%20teachers%20are%20able%20to%20organize%2C%20and%20whether%20the%20state%20has%20laws%20that%20protect%20workers%20from%20employer%20retaliation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20right%20to%20organize%20has%20been%20particularly%20controversial%20in%20the%20South%20in%20recent%20years.%20The%20Republican%20governors%20of%20Alabama%2C%20Georgia%2C%20and%20Tennessee%20have%20all%20passed%20laws%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Falabamareflector.com%2F2024%2F04%2F24%2Falabama-house-oks-sanctions-for-companies-that-voluntarily-recognize-unions%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estripping%20away%20state%20incentives%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20companies%20that%20voluntarily%20recognize%20labor%20unions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20GOP%20governors%20of%20South%20Carolina%2C%20Texas%2C%20and%20Mississippi%20joined%20the%20aforementioned%20states%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgovernor.alabama.gov%2Fnewsroom%2F2024%2F04%2Fgovernor-ivey-other-southern-governors-issue-joint-statement-in-opposition-to-united-auto-workers-uaws-unionization-campaign%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eissuing%20a%20statement%3C%2Fa%3E%20deriding%20the%20United%20Auto%20Workers%20campaign%20to%20organize%20workers%20at%20car%20manufacturing%20plants%20across%20the%20South.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOxfam%20gave%20Texas%2C%20South%20Carolina%2C%20and%20Georgia%20a%20score%20of%20zero%20out%20of%20one%20hundred%20on%20rights%20to%20organize%2C%20while%20Tennessee%2C%20Mississippi%2C%20and%20Alabama%20earned%20a%20score%20of%2010.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-us-states-high-wages-salaries-worker-rights-california-2024-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1724925362000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66cf2d3c1aa2ac29ee34ec82%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-us-states-high-wages-salaries-worker-rights-california-2024-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20flood%20of%20workers%20have%20moved%20south%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20but%20many%20southern%20states%20offer%20lower%20wages%20and%20fewer%20worker%20protections.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Juliana%20Kaplan%2CEliza%20Relman)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-us-states-high-wages-salaries-worker-rights-california-2024-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20best%20way%20to%20fix%20your%20credit%20score%3F%20Ignore%20it.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20anxious%20person%20scrutinizing%20a%20credit%20score%20meter%2C%20with%20a%20needle%20pointing%20to%20a%20good%20rating.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66cf6bca43b5e59d16b61510%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20Alyssa%20Powell%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWorried%20about%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fcredit-score%2Fwhat-is-a-credit-score%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecredit%20score%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%20Maybe%20you%20weren't%20before%2C%20but%20now%20that%20I%20mention%20it%20you%20may%20be%20wondering%20when%20the%20last%20time%20you%20checked%20it%20was.%20Even%20if%20you're%20pretty%20sure%20it's%20fine%2C%20the%20topic%20is%20often%20enough%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffinancial-therapist-talk-about-anxiety-money-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecause%20a%20moment%20of%20panic%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20sinking%20feeling%20followed%20by%20an%20%26quot%3BOh%20God%2C%20what%20if%20something's%20happened%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20little%20three-digit%20number%20is%20a%20big%20deal%20in%20our%20financial%20lives.%20It%20serves%20as%20a%20sort%20of%20grade%20for%20how%20you%20handle%20money.%20An%20A%20gets%20you%20approval%20for%20an%20apartment%20and%20a%20decent%20rate%20on%20your%20car%20loan%3B%20an%20F%20gets%20your%20rental%20application%20turned%20down%20and%20makes%20your%20car%20insurance%20more%20expensive.%20You%20might%20not%20have%20even%20realized%20it%2C%20but%20your%20credit%20report%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-cleaning-up-your-credit-can-help-you-land-a-job-2013-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecould%20even%20make%20a%20difference%20in%20whether%20you%20land%20your%20next%20job%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20anxiety%20around%20credit%20scores%20is%20palpable.%20It's%20also%20lucrative.%20Credit%20bureaus%2C%20startups%2C%20and%20even%20one-man%20operations%20can%20make%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20by%20playing%20into%20people's%20fears%20about%20their%20credit.%20They%20offer%20services%20that%20monitor%20credit%20scores%20and%20alert%20you%20when%20yours%20changes%2C%20or%20they%20say%20they%20can%20help%20you%20repair%20your%20damaged%20credit%20%E2%80%94%20for%20a%20price%2C%20of%20course.%20Many%20of%20these%20costly%20solutions%20do%20not%20work%20as%20well%20as%20promised%20or%20deliver%20much%2C%20if%20any%2C%20bang%20for%20your%20buck.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20credit-scoring%20companies%20have%20figured%20out%20how%20to%20profit%20on%20the%20anxiety%20of%20consumers%20with%20credit%20watch%20and%20credit%20monitoring%20and%20all%20of%20these%20add-on%20programs%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Aaron%20Klein%2C%20a%20senior%20fellow%20in%20economic%20studies%20at%20the%20Brookings%20Institution%2C%20a%20nonpartisan%20think%20tank.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20companies%20find%20a%20way%20to%20profit%20off%20of%20anxiety%2C%20they%20have%20an%20incentive%20to%20create%20anxiety.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20these%20companies%20won't%20tell%20you%20is%20that%20the%20best%20things%20to%20help%20ease%20your%20credit-related%20worries%20are%20cheap%2C%20even%20free.%20You%20can%20check%20your%20credit%20regularly%20at%20no%20cost%20from%20a%20lot%20of%20sources%20%E2%80%94%20your%20credit-card%20company%20likely%20tells%20you%20your%20score%2C%20and%20you%20can%20access%20your%20report%20weekly%20free%20of%20charge%20too.%20Freezing%20your%20credit%20also%20doesn't%20run%20you%20anything.%20It's%20important%20to%20be%20aware%20of%20your%20credit%20score%2C%20but%20you%20don't%20need%20to%20obsess%20over%20it%20%E2%80%94%20or%20let%20marketers%20convince%20you%20to%20pay%20for%20a%20bunch%20of%20stuff%20you%20don't%20really%20need%20because%20you're%20panicked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EAround%20the%20time%20of%20the%20Super%20Bowl%2C%20I%20noticed%20that%20the%20Kansas%20City%20Chiefs%20tight%20end%20Travis%20Kelce%20was%20appearing%20in%20ads%20for%20Experian%2C%20one%20of%20the%20big%20three%20bureaus%20responsible%20for%20keeping%20track%20of%20everyone's%20credit%20scores.%20I%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftravis-kelce-experian-tv-commercials-nfl-taylor-swift-super-bowl-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edecided%20to%20write%20about%20it%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%2C%20in%20the%20process%2C%20created%20an%20Experian%20account.%20The%20company%20has%20been%20hounding%20me%20ever%20since.%20I%20get%20near-daily%20emails%20that%20range%20from%20run-of-the-mill%20product%20offers%20and%20%26quot%3Bcredit%20alerts%26quot%3B%20to%20nerve-racking%20warnings%20that%20my%20information%20may%20have%20been%20part%20of%20a%20data%20breach.%20When%20I%20click%20for%20more%20information%2C%20lo%20and%20behold%2C%20I'm%20confronted%20with%20a%20paid%20service.%20For%20%2425%20a%20month%2C%20I%20can%20sign%20up%20for%20%26quot%3BExperian%20CreditWorks%20Premium%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20includes%20quarterly%20credit%20reports%2C%20credit%20monitoring%2C%20and%20identity%20protection.%20Once%20I%20decline%20that%20offer%2C%20which%20is%20kind%20of%20tricky%2C%20I%20can%20also%20find%20an%20offer%20to%20%26quot%3Block%26quot%3B%20my%20credit%20for%20%245%20a%20month.%20It's%20similar%20to%20a%20credit%20freeze%2C%20which%20blocks%20creditors%20from%20accessing%20your%20credit%20file%2C%20but%20can%20also%20do%20things%20like%20notify%20you%20if%20someone%20tries%20to%20access%20your%20Experian%20credit%20report.%20Here's%20the%20thing%2C%20though%3A%20A%20lot%20of%20the%20services%20it's%20offering%20are%20already%20free.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20no%20reason%20ever%20to%20pay%20for%20credit%20monitoring%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Chi%20Chi%20Wu%2C%20a%20senior%20attorney%20at%20the%20National%20Consumer%20Law%20Center.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20no%20reason%20to%20pay%20for%20a%20credit%20score%20or%20pay%20for%20service%20for%20the%20credit%20score.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Wu's%20view%2C%20Experian%20is%20an%20especially%20bad%20offender%20%E2%80%94%20not%20just%20for%20its%20suite%20of%20likely%20unnecessary%20products%20but%20because%2C%20as%20part%20of%20its%20standard%20agreement%2C%20the%20company%20makes%20customers%20agree%20to%20mandatory%20arbitration%2C%20meaning%20you%20don't%20get%20to%20sue%20if%20Experian%20has%20a%20big%20screwup%20later.%20In%20an%20email%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20Experian%20said%20that%20the%20company%20is%20%26quot%3Bcommitted%20to%20financial%20inclusion%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20its%20free%20membership%20has%20tools%20to%20help%20consumers%20improve%20their%20financial%20health.%20%26quot%3BMillions%20of%20members%20find%20value%20in%20having%20Experian%20as%20their%20financial%20co-pilot%20helping%20them%20improve%2C%20manage%2C%20and%20protect%20their%20financial%20profile%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20said.%20They%20did%20not%20address%20the%20arbitration%20agreement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Experian%20is%20hardly%20the%20only%20company%20out%20there%20selling%20credit-related%20services%20that%20drain%20consumer%20dollars.%20The%20credit-monitoring%20and%20identity-theft-protection%20industry%2C%20according%20to%20IBISWorld%2C%20is%20worth%20about%20%245.4%20billion%20in%20annual%20revenue.%20The%20growth%20of%20the%20industry%20makes%20sense%20%E2%80%94%20in%20this%20day%20and%20age%2C%20data%20breaches%20are%20constant%2C%20and%20a%20fraudulent%20ding%20on%20your%20credit%20report%20or%20someone%20opening%20an%20account%20in%20your%20name%20can%20be%20an%20enormous%20headache.%20Guarding%20against%20that%20outcome%20seems%20like%20a%20small%20price%20to%20pay%20for%20a%20lot%20of%20people%2C%20except%20that%20paying%20any%20price%20above%20%240%20may%20not%20actually%20be%20worth%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nclc.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F09%2FIB_Credit_Monitoring_Arbitration.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2022%20brief%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20NCLC%20described%20credit-monitoring%20bundles%20as%20often%20%26quot%3Bexpensive%20and%20ineffective%26quot%3B%20and%20argued%20that%20they%20failed%20to%20meaningfully%20benefit%20consumers.%20It%20noted%20that%20most%20identity%20theft%20takes%20place%20in%20existing%20accounts%2C%20meaning%20monitoring%20services%20that%20alert%20consumers%20to%20newly%20opened%20accounts%20miss%20it.%20They%20also%20often%20fail%20to%20catch%20fraud%20related%20to%20medical%20services%20or%20tax%20refunds.%20And%20even%20when%20they%20do%20catch%20identity%20theft%2C%20they%20do%20so%20after%20the%20fact.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20people%20might%20be%20like%2C%20'Well%2C%20I'd%20rather%20pay%20and%20not%20deal%20with%20the%20time%2C'%26quot%3B%20Wu%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20the%20thing%20is%20those%20products%20aren't%20all%20that%20effective.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gao.gov%2Fassets%2Fgao-17-254.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2017%20report%20from%20the%20Government%20Accountability%20Office%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20pretty%20negative%20on%20the%20whole%20monitoring%20and%20identity-theft-protection%20business%2C%20too%2C%20saying%20it's%20just%20not%20clear%20how%20helpful%20a%20lot%20of%20this%20stuff%20is.%20The%20report%20also%20looked%20at%20identity-theft%20insurance%20and%20noted%20that%20while%20it%20covered%20expenses%20related%20to%20dealing%20with%20the%20theft%2C%20it%20generally%20excluded%20actual%20financial%20losses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20credit%20monitoring%20falls%20into%20the%20waste-of-money%20category%2C%20other%20credit-related%20services%20can%20cross%20over%20into%20potentially%20predatory%20territory%20%E2%80%94%20for%20example%2C%20credit-repair%20operations.%20The%20idea%20behind%20these%20services%20is%20pretty%20simple%3A%20Credit%20reports%20often%20include%20some%20mistakes%20that%20can%20ding%20people's%20scores.%20So%2C%20for%20a%20fee%2C%20the%20companies%20will%20dispute%20a%20bunch%20of%20items%20in%20hopes%20of%20boosting%20the%20score.%20This%20may%20improve%20people's%20reports%20temporarily%20while%20the%20disputes%20are%20being%20investigated%2C%20but%20since%20the%20firms%20are%20basically%20disputing%20anything%20negative%2C%20when%20they%20lose%2C%20everything%20goes%20back%20to%20how%20it%20was%2C%20and%20the%20customer%20is%20just%20out%20more%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20basically%20charging%20people%20with%20the%20false%20promise%20that%20they're%20going%20to%20be%20able%20to%20fix%20their%20credit%20reports%20and%20credit%20scores%20permanently%20when%20they%20can't%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Sarah%20Chenven%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Working%20Credit%2C%20a%20nonprofit%20that%20helps%20people%20build%20credit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECredit-repair%20companies%20often%20target%20people%20with%20lower%20incomes%20and%20people%20desperate%20to%20improve%20their%20credit%20reports%20and%20scores.%20Gen%20Zers%20and%20millennials%2C%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.creditkarma.com%2Finsights%2Fi%2Fstate-of-debt-and-credit-report%23average-credit-scores%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etend%20to%20have%20lower%20credit%20scores%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20older%20generations%20and%20may%20not%20have%20extensive%20credit%20files%2C%20may%20be%20more%20likely%20to%20find%20themselves%20looking%20at%20a%20credit-repair%20service%20to%20get%20negative%20items%20off%20their%20reports%20or%20at%20some%20sort%20of%20credit-building%20service%20to%20just%20help%20them%20develop%20a%20record.%20Credit-monitoring%20companies%20can%20really%20appeal%20to%20anyone%20worried%20about%20their%20credit%20and%20identity%20theft.%20Some%20of%20these%20businesses%20also%20make%20money%20by%20marketing%20various%20financial%20products%20to%20people%20%E2%80%94%20a%20well-off%20boomer%20might%20get%20one%20type%20of%20credit-card%20offer%2C%20a%20struggling%20student%20another.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20companies%20also%20don't%20do%20anything%20people%20can't%20do%20on%20their%20own%20%E2%80%94%20if%20there's%20an%20error%2C%20you%20can%20and%20should%20dispute%20it%20yourself.%20In%20fact%2C%20credit-repair%20agencies%20can%20be%20less%20effective%20than%20the%20average%20person%20at%20getting%20mistakes%20wiped%20from%20their%20credit%20histories%20because%2C%20as%20Andrew%20Pizor%2C%20a%20senior%20attorney%20at%20the%20NCLC%2C%20explained%2C%20the%20law%20says%20that%20credit-reporting%20agencies%20have%20to%20respond%20only%20to%20dispute%20letters%20directly%20from%20consumers.%20Credit-repair%20businesses%20try%20really%20hard%20to%20make%20it%20seem%20like%20disputes%20are%20from%20consumers%2C%20and%20the%20agencies%20try%20just%20as%20hard%20to%20sniff%20out%20whether%20that's%20going%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMost%20of%20the%20letters%20that%20you're%20paying%20for%20are%20going%20into%20the%20garbage%2C%26quot%3B%20Pizor%20said.%20He%20added%20that%20if%20your%20dispute%20letters%20are%20going%20unanswered%2C%20you%20don't%20need%20a%20repair%20service%20%E2%80%94%20you%20need%20a%20lawyer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFederal%20regulators%20have%20gone%20after%20several%20companies%20accused%20of%20playing%20it%20fast%20and%20loose%20with%20the%20way%20they%20approach%20consumers.%20In%202017%2C%20the%20Consumer%20Financial%20Protection%20Bureau%20settled%20with%20TransUnion%20over%20charges%20related%20to%20how%20it%20was%20marketing%20its%20products%2C%20including%20credit%20monitoring%2C%20and%20ordered%20it%20to%20stop%20deceptive%20practices.%20In%202022%2C%20it%20sued%20TransUnion%2C%20accusing%20it%20of%20violating%20that%20order.%20In%202005%2C%20it%20dinged%20Experian%20for%20marketing%20free%20credit%20reports%20that%20weren't%20so%20free.%20Last%20year%2C%20the%20CFPB%20entered%20into%20a%20%242.7%20billion%20settlement%20with%20a%20ring%20of%20credit-repair%20brands%20accused%20of%20illegally%20collecting%20fees%20for%20their%20services.%20Over%20a%20decade%20ago%2C%20the%20Federal%20Trade%20Commission%20and%2035%20states%20reached%20a%20%2412%20million%20settlement%20with%20LifeLock%20after%20alleging%20that%20it%20had%20made%20false%20claims%20about%20its%20identity-theft-protection%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20companies%20and%20credit-related%20services%20aren't%20necessarily%20evil.%20A%20significant%20part%20of%20the%20issue%20is%20that%20the%20ecosystem%20is%20a%20mess.%20Our%20credit-reporting%20and%20-scoring%20system%20is%20outdated%20and%20confusing%2C%20and%20so%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20businesses%20that%20have%20sprung%20from%20it.%20Even%20the%20seemingly%20good%20products%20and%20services%20out%20there%20are%20a%20sign%20of%20the%20deep%20rot%20at%20the%20core%20of%20the%20whole%20system.%20Credit-building%20loans%2C%20which%20are%20loans%20designed%20to%20help%20people%20without%20much%20credit%20history%20build%20some%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.consumerfinance.gov%2Fdata-research%2Fresearch-reports%2Ftargeting-credit-builder-loans%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecan%20help%20people%20get%20on%20better%20financial%20footing%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20even%20if%20there%20is%20usually%20some%20cost%20involved.%20Immigrants%20and%20young%20people%20in%20particular%20can%20benefit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20such%20as%20Credit%20Karma%20that%20let%20you%20access%20a%20lot%20of%20your%20information%20easily%20and%20for%20free%20make%20it%20so%20your%20credit%20score%20isn't%20such%20a%20mystery.%20The%20downside%20there%20is%20that%20they%20make%20their%20money%20by%20giving%20your%20information%20to%20a%20bunch%20of%20third-party%20financial%20products%20and%20taking%20a%20cut%20if%20you%20sign%20up%20for%20one%20of%20them.%20For%20consumers%2C%20the%20whole%20thing%20feels%20like%20a%20maze.%20It's%20tough%20to%20separate%20the%20good%20actors%20from%20the%20bad%20and%20to%20understand%20the%20trade-offs%20at%20hand.%20It's%20not%20always%20clear%20what%20you're%20signing%20up%20for%2C%20whether%20you%20need%20it%2C%20or%20what%20you're%20going%20to%20wind%20up%20paying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20credit%20system%20and%20the%20financial%20system%2C%20and%20I%20hate%20to%20sound%20a%20little%20preachy%2C%20but%20it's%20a%20black%20box%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Ryan%20Steckler%2C%20a%20vice%20president%20of%20product%20and%20general%20manager%20at%20Credit%20Karma.%20%26quot%3BGiven%20that%20situation%2C%20we're%20in%20the%20business%20of%20empowering%20our%20consumers%20by%20giving%20them%20access%20to%20the%20same%20data%20those%20financial%20institutions%20have.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20would%20be%20neat%20to%20be%20able%20to%20say%20that%20some%20concrete%20help%20is%20on%20the%20way%2C%20but%20the%20truth%20is%20we're%20stuck%20with%20some%20not-so-fun%20realities%20around%20credit%20scores%20for%20the%20foreseeable%20future.%20As%20screwed%20up%20as%20the%20system%20is%2C%20it's%20probably%20not%20going%20anywhere%20anytime%20soon%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.investopedia.com%2Fterms%2Fc%2Fcash-flow-underwriting.asp%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeven%20though%20there%20are%20better%20alternatives%20out%20there%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20this%20sense%20of%20existential%20dread%20around%20credit%20scores.%20A%20negative%20one%20can%20really%20drag%20people%20down.%20An%20impaired%20record%20makes%20loans%20more%20expensive%2C%20makes%20accessing%20certain%20financial%20products%20impossible%2C%20and%20may%20even%20put%20your%20next%20apartment%20or%20job%20out%20of%20reach.%20Klein%2C%20from%20the%20Brookings%20Institution%2C%20has%20recently%20been%20conducting%20focus%20groups%20with%20low-income%20consumers%20about%20their%20financial%20knowledge%20and%20concerns.%20He's%20been%20shocked%20at%20how%20much%20credit%20scores%20have%20come%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20very%20surprised%20at%20the%20attention%20to%20detail%20folks%20of%20more%20modest%20income%20have%20on%20the%20impact%20of%20financial%20products%20and%20choices%20on%20their%20credit%20scores%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20more%20I%20thought%20about%20it%2C%20the%20more%20I%20realized%20this%20focus%20is%20based%20on%20experience.%20At%20some%20point%2C%20their%20low%20credit%20score%20has%20negatively%20impacted%20their%20lives.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrederick%20Wherry%2C%20a%20Princeton%20sociologist%20who%20leads%20the%20Debt%20Collection%20Lab%2C%20an%20initiative%20focused%20on%20understanding%20debt%20collection%2C%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BAs%20soon%20as%20we%20are%20asked%20about%20our%20credit%20scores%2C%20or%20in%20a%20moment%20when%20we%20can't%20get%20something%20we%20need%20or%20we%20get%20it%20at%20too%20high%20a%20price%2C%20that's%20when%20we%20realize%20that%20this%20thing%20has%20been%20hanging%20over%20our%20heads.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20unwise%20to%20bury%20your%20head%20in%20the%20sand%2C%20ignore%20your%20credit%20score%2C%20and%20hope%20for%20the%20best.%20But%20you%20don't%20need%20to%20obsess%20over%20it%2C%20let%20alone%20spend%20a%20bunch%20of%20money%20on%20it.%20If%20you're%20not%20in%20the%20market%20for%20a%20house%20or%20apartment%20or%20in%20need%20of%20a%20new%20loan%2C%20you%20can%20freeze%20your%20credit%20for%20free%2C%20meaning%20no%20fraudsters%20can%20take%20out%20a%20loan%20in%20your%20name.%20Under%20federal%20law%2C%20the%20bureaus%20have%20to%20give%20you%20one%20free%20credit%20report%20a%20year%2C%20and%20since%20the%20pandemic%20they've%20been%20letting%20people%20access%20their%20reports%20for%20free%20once%20a%20week.%20If%20you%20see%20something%20weird%20on%20your%20report%2C%20you%20can%20dispute%20it%20on%20your%20own.%20And%20you%20really%20do%20not%20need%20to%20be%20checking%20that%20much%20%E2%80%94%20once%20a%20month%20or%20once%20a%20quarter%20is%20fine%2C%20kind%20of%20like%20your%20401(k).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20have%20a%20credit%20score%20over%20720%20or%20780%2C%20stop%20worrying.%20Don't%20be%20obsessed%20with%20getting%20an%20800%20or%20820%2C%26quot%3B%20Wu%20said.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20not%20your%20SAT%20score.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20in%20trouble%2C%20there%20are%20nonprofits%20out%20there%20that%20can%20help%20you%20figure%20out%20what%20to%20do%2C%20for%20little%20or%20no%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you've%20got%20bad%20credit%2C%20if%20your%20credit%20score%20is%20low%2C%20where%20I'd%20start%20is%20with%20a%20nonprofit%20credit%20counselor%2C%26quot%3B%20Pizor%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20want%20to%20sign%20up%20for%20identity-theft%20protection%20or%20credit%20monitoring%2C%20fine.%20But%20those%20services%20aren't%20a%20fail-safe%2C%20so%20you'll%20want%20to%20walk%20in%20with%20your%20eyes%20wide%20open.%20The%20credit%20experts%20I%20spoke%20with%20were%20very%20wary%20about%20credit%20repair%20across%20the%20board.%20The%20next%20time%20you%20start%20to%20worry%20about%20your%20credit%20score%2C%20take%20a%20beat.%20Not%20to%20get%20too%20woo-woo%20here%2C%20but%20really%2C%20there's%20only%20so%20much%20you%20can%20control.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20mean%2C%20the%20magic%20bullet%20is%20building%20a%20better%20system%2C%26quot%3B%20Wu%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femily-stewart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEmily%20Stewart%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%2C%20writing%20about%20business%20and%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%