on%20of%20antitrust%20laws.%20Meanwhile%2C%20short-term%20profits%20reign%20supreme%20on%20Wall%20Street%2C%20and%20the%20oil%20and%20gas%20industry%20continues%20to%20be%20high%20risk%2C%20high%20reward.%20After%20the%20start%20of%20Russia's%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20in%202022%2C%20gas%20prices%20soared%20as%20Europe%20clamored%20for%20US%20supplies%20of%20the%20fuel%2C%20leading%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.energymonitor.ai%2Ffinance%2Fbig-oil-profits-soared-to-nearly-200bn-in-2022%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecord%20%24200%20billion%20in%20profit%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20Western%20oil%20and%20gas%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20all%20these%20factors%2C%20it's%20not%20that%20surprising%20that%20some%20firms%20are%20backtracking%2C%20said%20Adair%20Turner%2C%20the%20chair%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.energy-transitions.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEnergy%20Transitions%20Commission%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20think%20tank%20focused%20on%20climate%20action%20and%20economic%20growth%20that%20counts%20banks%20such%20as%20HSBC%20and%20Bank%20of%20America%20as%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCompanies%20can%20be%20very%20powerful%20drivers%20of%20change%2C%20and%20they%20can%20help%20convince%20politicians%20what's%20possible%2C%26quot%3B%20Turner%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20if%20there%20is%20a%20big%20backsliding%20on%20the%20political%20side%2C%20you%20will%20see%20a%20big%20backsliding%20on%20business%20as%20well.%20That's%20just%20the%20world%20we%20live%20in.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Wall%20Street's%20biggest%20firms%20made%20their%20net-zero%20promises%2C%20the%20oil%20and%20gas%20industry%20wasn't%20doing%20so%20hot.%20The%20COVID-19%20shutdowns%20had%20triggered%20the%20third%20major%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fcommodities%2Fgas-oil-prices-outlook-supply-shock-us-production-crude-forecast-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eenergy-price%3C%2Fa%3E%20collapse%20in%20a%20dozen%20years%2C%20and%20corporate%20America%20woke%20up%20to%20the%20risks%20that%20climate-fueled%20disasters%20posed%20to%20their%20investments.%20In%20his%20closely%20read%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.blackrock.com%2Fcorporate%2Finvestor-relations%2F2020-larry-fink-ceo-letter%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eannual%20letter%20to%20shareholders%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202020%2C%20BlackRock%20CEO%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkey-takeaways-blackrock-ceo-larry-finks-letter-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELarry%20Fink%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20whose%20firm%20manages%20more%20than%20%2410%20trillion%20in%20assets%20and%20is%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20shareholders%20in%20many%20companies%2C%20said%20his%20firm%20was%20putting%20climate%20risk%20and%20sustainability%20at%20the%20center%20of%20its%20investment%20approach%20and%20would%20increasingly%20hold%20corporate%20boards%20accountable%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.blackrock.com%2Fcorporate%2Finvestor-relations%2F2020-larry-fink-ceo-letter%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efor%20not%20disclosing%20and%20managing%20climate%20risks%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Bank%20of%20America%20won%20praise%20from%20climate%20advocates%20when%20it%20said%20it%20would%20no%20longer%20directly%20finance%20new%20coal%20mines%2C%20coal-fired%20power%20plants%2C%20or%20Arctic%20drilling%20projects.%20Citi%20CEO%20Jane%20Fraser%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Fcitigroups-jane-fraser-expects-to-shed-some-clients-for-climate-purposes-11638912251%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20The%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20December%202021%20that%20meeting%20net-zero%20goals%20may%20mean%20cutting%20off%20some%20clients.%20Beyond%20individual%20efforts%2C%20Wall%20Street%20also%20came%20together%20in%20collective%20climate%20initiatives.%20The%20investor%20group%20Climate%20Action%20100%2B%20pressured%20companies%20to%20disclose%20their%20climate%20risks%20and%20emissions.%20The%20Glasgow%20Financial%20Alliance%20for%20Net%20Zero%20convened%20in%202021%20and%20required%20members%20to%20commit%20to%20net-zero%20emissions%2C%20have%20a%20science-based%20plan%20for%20how%20to%20get%20there%2C%20and%20regularly%20report%20progress.%20Firms%20representing%20some%2040%25%20of%20global%20financial%20assets%20joined%2C%20including%20Citi%2C%20JPMorgan%20Chase%2C%20Bank%20of%20America%2C%20BlackRock%2C%20State%20Street%2C%20and%20Vanguard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20by%202022%2C%20cracks%20began%20to%20emerge.%20That%20year%2C%20GFANZ%20dropped%20a%20requirement%20that%20members%20align%20with%20the%20UN%20Race%20to%20Zero%20campaign%20after%20it%20required%20more%20aggressive%20climate%20actions%2C%20including%20phasing%20out%20financing%20for%20new%20fossil-fuel%20assets%20that%20weren't%20paired%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-steel-carbon-capture-does-it-work-reduce-emissions-controversial-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecarbon-capture%20technology%3C%2Fa%3E.%20People%20familiar%20with%20the%20fallout%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20GFANZ%20members%20were%20blindsided%20by%20the%20changes%20and%20didn't%20want%20to%20be%20beholden%20to%20criteria%20created%20by%20a%20small%20group%20of%20UN%20experts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndividual%20banks%20have%20also%20adjusted%20some%20of%20their%20climate%20policies.%20Bank%20of%20America%20in%20late%202023%20quietly%20dropped%20its%20policy%20on%20coal%20and%20Arctic%20drilling%20and%20said%20it%20would%20instead%20subject%20those%20projects%20to%20%26quot%3Benhanced%20due%20diligence.%26quot%3B%20That%20year%2C%20BlackRock%20also%20appointed%20Saudi%20Aramco%20CEO%20Amin%20Nasser%20to%20its%20board%2C%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbc.ca%2Fnews%2Fcanada%2Fcalgary%2Fbakx-ceraweek-saudi-aramco-exxon-1.7147290%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecently%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20should%20abandon%20the%20fantasy%20of%20phasing%20out%20oil%20and%20gas.%26quot%3B%20Even%20Fink%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.blackrock.com%2Fcorporate%2Finvestor-relations%2Flarry-fink-annual-chairmans-letter%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20his%20latest%20letter%20to%20investors%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20emphasized%20%26quot%3Benergy%20pragmatism%2C%26quot%3B%20where%20countries%20don't%20have%20to%20choose%20between%20renewable%20energy%20or%20fossil%20fuels%20but%20can%20have%20both%2C%20albeit%20less%20of%20the%20latter.%20Earlier%20this%20year%2C%20BlackRock%20scaled%20back%20involvement%20in%20Climate%20Action%20100%2B%20by%20transferring%20its%20membership%20to%20an%20international%20subsidiary%2C%20while%20J.P.%20Morgan%20Asset%20Management%2C%20State%20Street%2C%20and%20Goldman%20Sachs%20Asset%20Management%20all%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.climateaction100.org%2Fnews%2Fclimate-action-100-reaction-to-recent-departures%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Equit%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20group%20as%20it%20started%20a%20%26quot%3Bphase%20two%26quot%3B%20strategy%20focused%20on%20investors%20asking%20companies%20to%20reduce%20emissions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20general%2C%20Wall%20Street%20views%20activists'%20requests%20as%20unrealistic%20and%20a%20poor%20reflection%20of%20the%20real%20economy.%20They%20firms%20argue%20that%20there's%20only%20so%20much%20a%20private%20financial%20institution%20can%20do%20when%20most%20governments%20aren't%20enacting%20policies%20to%20drastically%20slow%20demand%20for%20fossil%20fuels.%20Banks%20also%20can't%20dictate%20how%20and%20when%20companies%20decarbonize.%20Asset%20managers%20invest%20money%20on%20behalf%20of%20clients%2C%20who%20may%20or%20may%20not%20decide%20that%20the%20climate%20crisis%20is%20worth%20factoring%20into%20where%20they%20put%20their%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJPMorgan%20CEO%20Jamie%20Dimon%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jpmorganchase.com%2Fir%2Fannual-report%2F2023%2Far-ceo-letters%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%20a%20letter%20in%20April%20to%20shareholders%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20said%20stopping%20oil%20and%20gas%20projects%20was%20%26quot%3Bwrong%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Benormously%20naive%2C%26quot%3B%20calling%20out%20President%20Joe%20Biden's%20decision%20to%20pause%20the%20approval%20of%20new%20LNG%20terminals.%20Replacing%20coal%2C%20the%20most%20polluting%20fuel%2C%20with%20gas%20is%20one%20of%20the%20best%20ways%20to%20reduce%20carbon%20emissions%2C%20he%20said%2C%20and%20LNG%20exports%20are%20an%20economic%20boon%20for%20the%20US.%20While%20those%20comments%20weren't%20surprising%20%E2%80%94%20Dimon%20has%20long%20argued%20that%20oil%20and%20gas%20will%20need%20to%20stick%20around%20as%20the%20energy%20sector%20transitions%20%E2%80%94%20his%20vision%20for%20the%20bank's%20climate%20commitments%20did%20raise%20some%20eyebrows.%20Dimon%20indicated%20JPMorgan%20would%20use%20the%20word%20%26quot%3Bcommitment%26quot%3B%20less%20when%20discussing%20its%20climate%20goals%20and%20focus%20more%20on%20%26quot%3Baspirations%2C%26quot%3B%20in%20part%20because%20he%20said%20the%20financial%20sector%20could%20do%20only%20so%20much%20without%20more%20government%20action.%20The%20statement%20suggested%20JPMorgan%20was%20walking%20back%20its%20role%20in%20addressing%20the%20climate%20crisis%2C%20raising%20alarm%20among%20impact%20investors%2C%20climate%20advocates%2C%20and%20US%20Senate%20Democrats%20%E2%80%94%20who%20sent%20a%20letter%20accusing%20Dimon%20of%20losing%20faith%20in%20the%20private%20sector's%20ability%20to%20solve%20problems%20and%20said%20he%20owed%20the%20public%20an%20explanation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20for%20comment%2C%20JPMorgan%2C%20Bank%20of%20America%2C%20Citi%2C%20and%20BlackRock%20told%20BI%20that%20they%20remained%20committed%20to%20their%20net-zero%20plans.%20Dimon%2C%20in%20his%20April%20letter%2C%20said%20JPMorgan%20departed%20Climate%20Action%20100%2B%20because%20the%20bank%20now%20has%20its%20own%20environmental%2C%20social%2C%20and%20governance%20experts%2C%20while%20BlackRock%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.blackrock.com%2Fcorporate%2Fliterature%2Fpublication%2F2024-our-participation-in-climate-action-100.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eissued%20a%20statement%20in%20February%20saying%3C%2Fa%3E%20most%20of%20its%20clients%20with%20net-zero%20targets%20were%20in%20its%20international%20business.%20Citi%2C%20in%20a%20June%20letter%20to%20employees%20about%20the%20protests%2C%20said%20that%20it%20had%20deployed%20%24440%20billion%20in%20sustainable%20finance%20across%20a%20wide%20variety%20of%20areas%2C%20including%20renewable%20energy%2C%20with%20an%20aim%20to%20hit%20%241%20trillion%20by%202030%2C%20and%20that%20emissions%20tied%20to%20its%20energy%20portfolio%20had%20fallen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBanks'%20core%20role%20in%20the%20economy%20and%20the%20energy%20transition%20is%20facilitating%20access%20to%20capital%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20JPMorgan%20spokesperson%20said%2C%20citing%20the%20bank's%20%241%20trillion%20climate-finance%20target%20for%202030.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20proud%20of%20our%20ability%20to%20support%20our%20clients%20in%20their%20efforts%20towards%20a%20low-carbon%2C%20energy-rich%20future.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20BlackRock%20spokesperson%20said%20the%20firm's%20role%20is%20helping%20clients%20meet%20their%20unique%20investment%20goals%20and%20that%20assets%20in%20BlackRock's%20sustainable%20strategies%20had%20grown%20by%20more%20than%20760%25%20over%20the%20past%20five%20years.%20The%20firm%20also%20launched%20an%20option%20in%20July%20for%20clients%20who%20want%20their%20money%20to%20align%20with%20decarbonization.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Bank%20of%20America%20spokesperson%20said%20the%20company%20is%20supporting%20clients%20across%20the%20traditional%20and%20renewable%20energy%20sectors%20to%20drive%20innovation%20and%20help%20them%20meet%20transition%20goals.%20Bank%20of%20America%20has%20deployed%20%24560%20billion%20in%20sustainable%20finance%20with%20a%20goal%20to%20hit%20%241.5%20trillion%20by%202030.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20climate%20advocates%20said%20that%20the%20backsliding%20was%20deeply%20alarming%2C%20while%20others%20said%20the%20moves%20were%20more%20about%20managing%20optics%20to%20temper%20criticism%20from%20politicians%20on%20the%20right%20who%20could%20have%20more%20power%20if%20former%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20wins%20in%20November.%20Either%20way%2C%20Wall%20Street%20isn't%20acting%20fast%20enough%2C%20they%20said%2C%20and%20is%20spending%20too%20much%20time%20touting%20their%20green%20investments%2C%20while%20ignoring%20their%20unwillingness%20to%20stop%20providing%20massive%20amounts%20of%20funding%20for%20fossil%20fuels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20seen%20a%20lot%20of%20these%20companies%20get%20very%20excited%20about%20scaling%20up%20climate-solutions%20investments%20and%20lose%20sight%20of%20the%20importance%20of%20bringing%20down%20fossil-fuel%20emissions%2C%26quot%3B%20New%20York%20City's%20comptroller%2C%20Brad%20Lander%2C%20whose%20office%20oversees%20the%20investment%20of%20%24242%20billion%20in%20city%20pension%20funds%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20especially%20distressing%20at%20a%20firm%20like%20BlackRock%20because%20they're%20the%20biggest%20public-markets%20player.%20They%20are%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20investors%20in%20many%20of%20the%20highest-emitting%20companies.%20They%20need%20to%20demand%20real%20progress.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELander%20said%20he%20was%20encouraged%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcomptroller.nyc.gov%2Fnewsroom%2Fnyc-comptroller-lander-and-nyc-public-pension-boards-reach-agreement-on-climate-finance-disclosures-with-jpmorgan-chase-citi-and-royal-bank-of-canada%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAccording%2520to%2520research%2520by%2520Bloomberg%2Cof%25200.73%252Dto%252D1.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eagreements%20his%20office%20reached%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20year%20with%20JPMorgan%2C%20Citi%2C%20and%20Royal%20Bank%20of%20Canada%20for%20the%20banks%20to%20publicly%20disclose%20the%20ratio%20of%20money%20they%20put%20into%20clean%20energy%20versus%20fossil%20fuels.%20To%20prevent%20the%20world%20from%20warming%20to%20catastrophic%20levels%2C%20the%20International%20Energy%20Agency%20estimates%2C%20global%20investments%20in%20renewable%20energy%20need%20to%20outpace%20fossil%20fuels%20this%20decade%20by%204-to-1.%20In%20June%2C%20the%20agency%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iea.org%2Fnews%2Finvestment-in-clean-energy-this-year-is-set-to-be-twice-the-amount-going-to-fossil-fuels%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20the%20ratio%20across%20financial%20institutions%20globally%20would%20be%202-to-1%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20year%20in%20favor%20of%20renewables.%20The%20ratio%20at%20North%20American%20banks%20as%20of%202022%2C%20according%20to%20BloombergNEF%2C%20was%20about%200.7-to-1.%20That%20ratio%20has%20likely%20changed%20after%20tax%20breaks%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsenate-manchin-schumer-climate-bill-cheaper-energy-cleaner-air-jobs-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunder%20the%20Inflation%20Reduction%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%20helped%20attract%20hundreds%20of%20billions%20of%20dollars%20of%20investment%20in%20the%20energy%20transition%2C%20but%20it's%20hard%20to%20know%20by%20how%20much%20because%20banks%20don't%20share%20their%20individual%20data.%20Lander%20said%20the%20new%20agreements%20would%20make%20it%20easier%20to%20see%20which%20banks%20are%20on%20track%20to%20meet%20their%20emissions-reduction%20pledges%20and%20which%20are%20not.%20This%20could%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20help%20the%20city's%20pension%20funds%20achieve%20net-zero%20emissions%20across%20their%20portfolios.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20some%20early%20signs%20that%20Wall%20Street%20may%20be%20turning%20a%20corner.%20The%20world's%2060%20largest%20banks%20collectively%20provided%20fewer%20loans%20and%20financial%20services%20to%20the%20fossil-fuel%20industry%20for%20two%20years%20in%20a%20row%2C%202022%20and%202023%2C%20the%20Banking%20on%20Climate%20Chaos%20report%20compiled%20by%20a%20network%20of%20climate%20groups%20said.%20But%20April%20Merleaux%2C%20a%20research%20manager%20at%20the%20Rainforest%20Action%20Network%20that%20spearheads%20the%20report%2C%20said%20she's%20skeptical%20the%20decline%20is%20here%20to%20stay%20for%20several%20reasons.%20Nearly%20half%20of%20those%20banks%20still%20increased%20financing%20between%202022%20and%202023%2C%20she%20said.%20Oil%20and%20gas%20companies%20also%20didn't%20need%20to%20borrow%20much%20money%20because%20they%20were%20sitting%20on%20so%20much%20cash%20following%20the%20global%20energy%20crisis.%20If%20that%20situation%20changes%2C%20there%20aren't%20many%20restrictions%20on%20banks%20ramping%20back%20up%20their%20fossil-fuel%20financing%2C%20at%20least%20not%20in%20the%20US.%20In%20Europe%2C%20stronger%20ESG%20laws%20and%20climate%20lawsuits%20have%20led%20banks%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ing.com%2FNewsroom%2FNews%2FING-takes-next-steps-on-energy-financing-after-COP28-1.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincluding%20ING%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20BNP%20Paribas%2C%20to%20set%20more%20aggressive%20policies%20to%20phase%20out%20financing%20for%20oil%20and%20gas%20exploration%20and%20production.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Homes%20surrounded%20in%20floodwater%20in%20Surfside%2C%20Texas%20after%20Hurricane%20Beryl.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66ce920343b5e59d16b5d6e8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHomes%20surrounded%20in%20floodwater%20in%20Surfside%2C%20Texas%20after%20Hurricane%20Beryl%20in%20July.%3Cp%3EBrandon%20Bell%2FGetty%20Images.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20we%20hear%20from%20banks%20is%20that%20their%20intention%20is%20to%20guide%20their%20clients%20on%20a%20net-zero%20journey%2C%26quot%3B%20Merleaux%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20that%20kind%20of%20engagement%20doesn't%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20teeth.%20If%20a%20client%20is%20not%20making%20meaningful%20decreases%20in%20its%20fossil-fuel%20business%2C%20will%20the%20bank%20cut%20them%20off%20or%20raise%20interest%20rates%20on%20their%20loans%20or%20any%20number%20of%20actions%20the%20banks%20could%20take%3F%20In%20some%20cases%2C%20they%20may%20be%20doing%20that%2C%20but%20there's%20no%20transparency.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECiti%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.citigroup.com%2Frcs%2Fcitigpa%2Fstorage%2Fpublic%2F2023-Citi-Climate-Report.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edisclosed%20earlier%20this%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%2042%25%20of%20its%20energy%20clients%20didn't%20have%20a%20%26quot%3Bsubstantive%26quot%3B%20transition%20plan%2C%20while%2029%25%20did%20have%20one%2C%20but%20it's%20unclear%20whether%20they%20can%20execute%20their%20strategies.%20The%20bank%20said%20it%20would%20support%20clients%20in%20improving%20those%20plans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-oil-production-boom-crude-supply-wti-price-goldman-sachs-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoil%20and%20gas%20production%20is%20on%20the%20rise%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20US%20produced%20record%20amounts%20last%20year%20and%20is%20set%20to%20nearly%20double%20its%20gas%20export%20capacity%20by%202028%2C%20when%20at%20least%20five%20more%20LNG%20terminals%20could%20be%20online.%20More%20than%20a%20dozen%20more%20have%20been%20proposed%2C%20mainly%20along%20the%20Gulf%20Coast%20in%20communities%20that%20have%20long%20been%20exposed%20to%20polluting%20oil%20and%20gas%20infrastructure.%20The%20liquid%20natural%20gas%20is%20destined%20for%20China%20and%20India%2C%20where%20demand%20is%20growing%2C%20as%20well%20as%20Europe%2C%20though%20wind%20and%20solar%20are%20pushing%20out%20fossil%20fuels%20quicker%20than%20expected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOil%20and%20gas%20production%20should%20decline%20by%2015%25%20and%2030%25%2C%20respectively%2C%20by%202030%20for%20the%20world%20to%20meet%20its%20climate%20goals%2C%20according%20to%20the%20IEA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20emissions%20rise%20alongside%20oil%20and%20gas%20production%2C%20so%20do%20the%20risks%20of%20economic%20destruction.%20Hurricanes%2C%20flooding%2C%20wildfires%2C%20drought%2C%20and%20extreme%20heat%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-climate-change-crisis-extreme-weather-is-costing-you-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eare%20becoming%20more%20costly%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20inflicting%20hundreds%20of%20billions%20of%20dollars%20in%20property%20damage%20over%20the%20past%20few%20years.%20Some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-insurers-will-shape-where-people-live-climate-change-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehomeowners%20in%20Florida%2C%20California%2C%20and%20Colorado%3C%2Fa%3E%20can't%20find%20affordable%20insurance%20because%20the%20risks%20are%20too%20high.%20Prices%20for%20coffee%2C%20chocolate%2C%20and%20olive%20oil%20have%20spiked%20because%20of%20higher%20temperatures%20and%20unpredictable%20rain.%20Businesses%20were%20less%20productive%20in%20recent%20years%20because%20of%20scorching%20hot%20temperatures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20told%2C%20the%20world%20could%20lose%2012%25%20of%20its%20GDP%20with%20every%20degree%20Celsius%20of%20warming%20above%201950s%20levels%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nber.org%2Fpapers%2Fw32450%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20working%20paper%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20National%20Bureau%20of%20Economic%20Research%20said.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.swissre.com%2Fpress-release%2FEconomic-losses-set-to-increase-due-to-climate-change-with-US-and-Philippines-the-hardest-hit-Swiss-Re-Institute-finds%2F3051a9b0-e379-4bcb-990f-3cc8236d55a1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einsurer%20Swiss%20Re%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20in%20February%20that%20the%20US%20economy%20already%20loses%200.4%25%20of%20its%20GDP%20annually%20because%20of%20severe%20floods%20and%20storms.%20The%20threat%20of%20financial%20losses%20makes%20Wall%20Street's%20support%20for%20oil%20and%20gas%20expansion%20paradoxical.%20Without%20a%20rapid%20shift%20away%20from%20fossil%20fuels%2C%20their%20bottom%20lines%20could%20suffer%20in%20the%20long%20term.%20Yet%20transitioning%20too%20quickly%20also%20comes%20with%20its%20own%20set%20of%20risks%2C%20given%20how%20many%20countries%20still%20rely%20on%20fossil%20fuels%20to%20power%20their%20economies.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ESure%2C%20financial%20institutions%20want%20to%20do%20the%20right%20thing%2C%20Turner%20of%20the%20Energy%20Transitions%20Commission%20said%2C%20but%20they%20worry%20that%20if%20they%20turn%20down%20oil%20and%20gas%20development%2C%20somebody%20else%20will%20finance%20it%20and%20take%20the%20profits.%20Governments%20have%20to%20step%20in%20to%20force%20Wall%20Street's%20hand%2C%20he%20added%2C%20or%20a%20cycle%20of%20promise%20making%20and%20backtracking%20will%20continue%20%E2%80%94%20until%20it's%20too%20late.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCompanies%20will%20always%20sit%20there%20with%20a%20tension%20between%2C%20'I%20want%20to%20make%20money%2C%20but%20I%20want%20to%20be%20able%20to%20look%20my%20grandchildren%20in%20the%20eye%2C'%26quot%3B%20Turner%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fcatherine-boudreau%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3ECatherine%20Boudreau%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20senior%20sustainability%20reporter%20at%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwall-street-banks-backtrack-climate-change-fighting-promises-2024-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1724923321000%2C%22