20and%20now%20spearheads%20Caltech's%20AI%20research.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20emphasizes%20the%20importance%20of%20open-source%20AI%20and%20regulating%20the%20technology.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20tech%20industry%20races%20to%20build%20language-learning%20models%20for%20AI%2C%20researcher%20Anima%20Anandkumar%20focuses%20on%20how%20AI%20can%20simulate%20the%20physical%20world%2C%20from%20predicting%20climate%20patterns%20to%20redesigning%20proteins%20in%20medicine.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20former%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnvidia-earnings-questions-product-delays-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENvidia%3C%2Fa%3E%20senior%20director%20of%20AI%20research%20and%20Amazon%20Web%20Services%20alum%20spent%20decades%20working%20at%20the%20forefront%20of%20AI%20algorithms%20and%20helped%20make%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnvidia-power-players-leaders-ai-chip-giant-success-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENvidia's%3C%2Fa%3E%20FourCastNet%20weather%20simulator%20available%20as%20open%20source.%20She%20has%20served%20as%20the%20Bren%20Professor%20in%20the%20computer%20science%20and%20mathematics%20department%20at%20Caltech%20since%202017%20and%20oversees%20the%20university's%20machine%20learning%20research%20efforts.%20Specifically%2C%20she%20focuses%20on%20tensors%2C%20a%20multilinear%20function%20that%20can%20help%20solve%20higher-order%20problems%20in%20AI%2C%20like%20modeling%20fluids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20has%20limits%20to%20what%20it%20can%20learn.%20If%20you%20ask%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-new-ai-chatbot-conversation-with-questions-answers-examples-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChatGPT%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20the%20weather%2C%20it%20will%20gather%20an%20answer%20from%20existing%20weather%20apps%20on%20the%20web.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20Anandkumar%20is%20researching%20how%20AI%20can%20more%20accurately%20simulate%20the%20weather%20and%20help%20give%20predictions%20for%20the%20climate%20crisis%20a%20decade%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20conversation%20with%20Business%20Insider%2C%20Anandkumar%20spoke%20about%20her%20academic%20research%20with%20neural%20operators%2C%20a%20network%20that%20maps%20between%20different%20AI%20functions%20and%20that%20can%20be%20used%20to%20model%20physical%20processes.%20She%20also%20explained%20why%20it's%20important%20to%20have%20a%20culture%20of%20open-sourcing%20AI%20in%20Big%20Tech.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20following%20was%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBI%3A%20You've%20fluidly%20gone%20through%20industry%20and%20academia%20most%20of%20your%20career.%20Why%20did%20you%20recently%20decide%20to%20leave%20Nvidia%20for%20academia%20full%20time%20whereas%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20are%20kind%20of%20going%20in%20the%20other%20direction%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20last%20decade%20or%20so%2C%20I've%20had%20a%20foot%20both%20in%20industry%20and%20academia.%20I%20see%20that%20as%20the%20golden%20age%20of%20open%20research%20where%20even%20in%20industry%2C%20you%20could%20open%20source%2C%20you%20could%20publish%2C%20you%20could%20freely%20collaborate.%20Unfortunately%2C%20since%20ChatGPT%20has%20come%20out%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20that%20has%20changed%20because%20there%20is%20a%20lot%20more%20push%20toward%20closed%20research%20and%20closed%20models%20in%20many%20of%20the%20Big%20Tech%20%5Bcompanies%5D.%20Even%20when%20models%20are%20getting%20open%20sourced%2C%20not%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20details%20are%20shown%20to%20the%20public%2C%20and%20so%20there%20are%20certainly%20big%20firewalls%20that%20are%20happening.%20To%20me%2C%20my%20goal%20to%20be%20having%20a%20dual%20appointment%20was%20to%20really%20enable%20open%20research%20and%20do%20that%20for%20beneficial%20tasks.%20We%20built%20our%20first%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3Da8147694bb1b296ebca63e2f5c7298093884f1252d2fa2a1cb1dea029431467c%26postID%3D66cb945bb6269761a73a49ed%26postSlug%3Danima-anandkumar-ai-climate-change-open-source-caltech-nvidia-2024-8%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nvidia.com%252Fen-us%252Fon-demand%252Fsession%252Fgtcspring22-d4113%252F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI-based%20weather%20model%3C%2Fa%3E.%20We%20built%20models%20for%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblogs.nvidia.com%2Fblog%2Fdrug-discovery-bionemo-generative-ai%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edrug%20discovery%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20are%20designing%20medical%20devices.%20All%20of%20this%20requires%20some%20openness%20once%20that%20is%20lacking%2C%20I%20felt%20like%20my%20true%20goal%20is%20to%20enhance%20the%20impact%20and%20benefit%20humanities.%20As%20cheesy%20as%20it%20sounds%2C%20I%20felt%20like%20this%20was%20a%20better%20way%20to%20do%20that.%20The%20notion%20is%20that%20there%20is%20a%20lot%20of%20computational%20spend%20to%20train%20large%20models%20and%20the%20aspect%20of%2C%20how%20do%20you%20monetize%20that.%20I'm%20not%20believing%20that%20to%20be%20a%20wrong%20goal%3B%20it%20just%20does%20not%20align%20with%20how%20I%20felt%20the%20best%20impact%20could%20be%20made.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBI%3A%20What%20is%20the%20day-to-day%20of%20doing%20research%20for%20industry%20versus%20now%20with%20Caltech%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECertainly%2C%20the%20resources%20are%20much%20fewer.%20Both%20at%20AWS%20and%20Nvidia%2C%20we%20had%20a%20lot%20of%20freedom%20to%20pursue%20new%20research%20areas.%20The%20computational%20resources%20are%20nowhere%20near%20what%20Big%20Tech%20has.%20To%20me%2C%20necessity%20is%20the%20mother%20of%20invention.%20So%20how%20do%20we%20build%20frameworks%20and%20algorithms%20that%20can%20do%20more%20with%20less%3F%20I%20think%20there's%20a%20lot%20of%20interesting%20research%20that%20will%20come%20out%20of%20academia%20in%20the%20next%20few%20years%20because%20that's%20the%20only%20way%20we%20can%20keep%20up%20with%20innovation%20in%20academia%20that%20won't%20be%20following%20the%20same%20approaches%20that%20the%20Big%20Techs%20are%20taking%2C%20but%20really%20thinking%20a%20lot%20more%20on%20how%20to%20make%20the%20algorithms%20more%20efficient.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBI%3A%20What%20are%20better%2C%20more%20'efficient'%20algorithms%2C%20and%20what%20are%20their%20broader%20impacts%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClever%20algorithms%20can%20come%20in%20many%20ways.%20One%20is%20being%20clever%20about%20how%20to%20make%20these%20algorithms%20efficient%2C%20not%20just%20having%20better%20hardware.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20aspect%20is%20to%20reduce%20the%20memory%20during%20training%20by%20doing%20cleverer%20optimization%20algorithms.%20You%20can%20drastically%20reduce%20the%20amount%20of%20memory%20needed%20so%20you%20can%20fit%20even%20fairly%20big%20models%20on%20much%20smaller%20GPUs%20or%20GPUs%20with%20lower%20memory%20that%20are%20cheaper.%20Sometimes%20you%20need%20to%20go%20back%20to%20the%20first%20principles%20and%20ask%2C%20are%20there%20some%20fundamental%20ways%20to%20completely%20rethink%20how%20we%20do%20this%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBI%3A%20In%20your%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ted.com%2Ftalks%2Fanima_anandkumar_ai_that_connects_the_digital_and_physical_worlds%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ETED%20Talk%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%2C%20you%20say%2C%20'Language%20models%20hallucinate%2C%20and%20they%20have%20no%20physical%20grounding.'%20Does%20this%20relate%20to%20any%20misconceptions%20that%20people%20have%20about%20AI%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EText%20does%20not%20encode%20all%20the%20knowledge%20in%20the%20world.%20It's%20the%20knowledge%20that%20humans%20have%20collected%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20the%20knowledge%20of%20the%20physical%20world.%20You%20can%20have%20all%20kinds%20of%20theories%20about%20playing%20tennis%20well%2C%20but%20the%20language%20model%20by%20itself%20cannot%20execute%20the%20action%20of%20playing%20tennis.%20Similarly%2C%20for%20weather%20forecasting%2C%20you%20can%20ask%20ChatGPT%20what%20the%20weather%20is%20tomorrow%2C%20and%20it%20can%20come%20up%20with%20an%20answer%2C%20but%20it%20will%20do%20that%20by%20looking%20up%20a%20weather%20app.%20It%20does%20not%20internally%20have%20the%20ability%20to%20simulate%20what%20happens%20to%20weather.%20It%20does%20not%20internally%20understand%20what%20is%20a%20hurricane.%20It%20can%20look%20up%20some%20text%20information%2C%20but%20it%20cannot%20go%20and%20simulate%20the%20physical%20process.%20Same%20with%20designing%20a%20better%20aircraft%20wing%20or%20a%20better%20rocket.%20You%20can%20ask%20any%20of%20the%20image%20generators%2C%20and%20they%20may%20give%20you%20the%20most%20fantastic-looking%20rocket%2C%20but%20I%20most%20likely%20will%20not%20be%20able%20to%20fly%20in%20the%20real%20world%20because%20those%20designs%20are%20not%20grounded%20in%20physics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBI%3A%20You%20talk%20a%20lot%20about%20neural%20operators.%20What%20are%20they%2C%20and%20how%20are%20they%20being%20used%20now%20in%20everyday%20life%20for%20the%20tech%20industry%20or%20other%20industries%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThink%20of%20it%20as%20extending%20the%20paradigm%20of%20deep%20learning%20to%20these%20continuous%20objects%3A%20the%20fact%20that%20now%20the%20Earth%20is%20not%20just%20a%20fixed%20set%20of%20pixels%2C%20but%20the%20Earth%20is%20really%20this%20continuous%20space.%20You%20can%20go%20and%20zoom%20in%20at%20any%20resolution%20and%20get%20answers%20at%20all%20those%20resolutions.%20That's%20how%20the%20whole%20physical%20world%20works.%20If%20you%20really%20think%20about%20the%20world%2C%20it%20happens%20at%20so%20many%20different%20scales.%20Think%20about%20even%20quantum%20effects%20that%20are%20needed%20for%20drug%20design%20and%20many%20very%20important%20practical%20problems.%20While%20really%20needing%20to%20have%20that%20ability%20to%20model%20weather%20and%20climate%2C%20we%20need%20to%20also%20model%20how%20these%20tiny%20particles%20in%20the%20cloud%20interact%20with%20one%20another.%20How%20do%20these%20vortices%20move%3F%20With%20standard%20AI%2C%20you%20can%20do%20top-down.%20In%20the%20case%20of%20weather%2C%20there's%20a%20lot%20of%20historical%20information%2C%20but%20you%20can%20be%20very%20blind.%20What%20we%20do%20with%20neural%20operators%20is%20to%20really%20combine%20the%20two%20paradigms%20you%20can%20both%20learn%20with%20the%20data%2C%20as%20well%20as%20add%20any%20of%20the%20physical%20knowledge%20you%20have%2C%20and%20do%20that%20at%20multiple%20resolutions%20so%20you%20can%20very%20accurately%20model%20these%20physical%20phenomena.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScientific%20research%2C%20engineering%20design%20in%20the%20past%20has%20been%20really%20about%20trial%20and%20error.%20Somebody%20you%20know%20comes%20up%20with%20an%20idea%2C%20but%20you%20have%20to%20go%20still%20test%20it%20in%20the%20lab%2C%20and%20the%20lab%20experiments%20can%20be%20very%20laborious%20and%20long%2C%20and%20not%20all%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENeural%20operators%20with%20an%20AI%20framework%20are%20a%20game%20changer%20because%20with%20this%2C%20you%20can%20build%20highly%20accurate%20digital%20twins.%20So%20instead%20of%20going%20to%20the%20lab%20and%20testing%20physically%2C%20now%20you%20have%20a%20digital%20twin%20that%20very%20accurately%20models%20very%20complex%20phenomena%20like%20fluid%20dynamics.%20And%20with%20that%2C%20the%20ability%20is%20to%20actually%20optimize%20design.%20So%20not%20only%20use%20this%20as%20a%20digital%20twin%20just%20to%20try%20out%20different%20possibilities%2C%20but%20ask%20it%20to%20generate%20the%20best%20design.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBI%3A%20What%20are%20some%20of%20the%20things%20that%20we%20should%20still%20be%20focusing%20on%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20democratizing%20AI%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20say%20democratization%2C%20that%20can%20be%20in%20terms%20of%20models%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-ai-llama-3-chatbot-mark-zuckerberg-existential-risks-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELlama%3C%2Fa%3E%20being%20openly%20available%2C%20but%20also%20the%20knowledge%20of%20how%20to%20train%20models%20is%20something%20that%20we%20need%20more%20in%20the%20open%20so%20we%20can%20carefully%20test%20and%20further%20develop%20the%20techniques%20because%20there%20are%20lots%20of%20big%20challenges%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20both%20language%20and%20all%20the%20other%20classes%20of%20models%2C%20too.%20That's%20where%2C%20you%20know%2C%20we%20want%20to%20be%20very%20careful%20not%20having%20regulations%20in%20place%20that%20harm%20open%20source%20and%20the%20small%20players.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20recently%20spearheaded%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdrive.google.com%2Ffile%2Fd%2F1OQVWpeg1qPPTYW43h662UsUhh8TxZbdp%2Fview%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eletter%20out%20of%20Caltech%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20stop%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fleginfo.legislature.ca.gov%2Ffaces%2FbillNavClient.xhtml%3Fbill_id%3D202320240SB1047%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESB-1047%20Bill%3C%2Fa%3E.%20(%3Cem%3ENote%3A%20SB-1047%20passed%20in%20the%20California%20state%20legislature%20on%20Wednesday%20and%20will%20go%20to%20Gov.%20Gavin%20Newsom%20for%20final%20consideration.)%20%3C%2Fem%3EMany%20other%20academics%20have%20made%20statements%2C%20and%20people%20in%20the%20industry%20have%20also%20come%20out%20against%20this%20bill.%20Even%20if%20there%20are%20good%20intentions%2C%20it's%20important%20to%20be%20careful%20that%20there%20can%20be%20unintended%20consequences.%20There%20is%20the%20notion%20of%20regulatory%20capture%2C%20where%20big%20companies%20can%20still%20deal%20with%20regulation%20by%20hiring%20a%20lot%20of%20people.%20And%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20startups%2C%20they%20are%20at%20a%20severe%20disadvantage.%20If%20you're%20effectively%20asking%20open%20source%20developers%20a%20lot%20in%20terms%20of%20if%20there's%20any%20harmful%20use%20downstream%20and%20that%20they%20would%20be%20responsible%2C%20then%20open%20source%20is%20effectively%20killed.%20That's%20not%20good%20for%20academia%2C%20either.%20AI%20has%20always%20been%20an%20open-source%20revolution%20from%20its%20early%20days%20because%20people%20created%20these%20data%20sets%20and%20held%20competitions%2C%20and%20everybody%20participated%2C%20did%20research%2C%20talked%20about%20it%2C%20shared%20the%20code.%20That's%20how%20the%20community%20just%20made%20these%20amazing%20developments%20in%20such%20a%20short%20amount%20of%20time.%20I%20think%20the%20way%20to%20be%20the%20right%20approach%20to%20doing%20this%20is%20not%20to%20think%20about%20regulating%20AI%2C%20but%20regulating%20harmful%20effects%20no%20matter%20what%20was%20used.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanima-anandkumar-ai-climate-change-open-source-caltech-nvidia-2024-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1724922002000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66cf87e0397a168972022d3c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanima-anandkumar-ai-climate-change-open-source-caltech-nvidia-2024-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22AI%20researcher%20Anima%20Anandkumar%20talks%20about%20the%20limitations%20of%20LLMs%2C%20AI%20applications%20for%20weather%20and%20climate%2C%20and%20the%20push%20for%20open%20source%20in%20Big%20Tech.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22hli%40businessinsider.com%20(Helen%20Li)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanima-anandkumar-ai-climate-change-open-source-caltech-nvidia-2024-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22United%20executive%20explains%20why%20the%20airline%20hasn't%20bought%20Boeing's%20newest%20widebody%20plane%22%2C%22conten